description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Northern Care Alliance NHS Group was created by bringing together staff and services from two NHS Trusts, Salford Royal NHS Foundation Trust and The Pennine Acute Hospitals NHS Trust. The sheer size, scale and potential of our combined service is huge. Together, we’ve a wealth of skills and resources to share and tap into and, a wide range of career paths for you to develop and explore. If you want to join a team of over 19,000 NHS experts in delivering high-quality, local care across Salford, Oldham, Bury and Rochdale and beyond – &lt;strong&gt;come and take your place with us.  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an opportunity for a forward thinking and dynamic Specialty Doctor to join the Ophthalmology service that provides outpatient and day case care to the populations of Bury, Oldham, Tameside and Rochdale. Day case surgery is provided from a purpose built eye unit at Rochdale Infirmary.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;You will have a broad experience of Ophthalmology and will join a team whose current interests include Cornea, Medical Retina, Glaucoma, Occuloplastics, Paediatrics and General Ophthalmology. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Participation to the 1:8 on call rota is required, contribution to the General Ophthalmic workload and have an interest in supporting the development of Ophthalmic care across the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span&gt;Mr Farhan Qureshi - Clinical Director &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Tel: 01706 517731  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Email:  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;farhan.qureshi@pat.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Or&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Gillian Ivey Directorate Manager &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Email:  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Gillian.Ivey@pat.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;All communications to applicants will be via the email address provided on your application form and all further correspondence will be through email, therefore please ensure that you regularly check your emails after the closing date for this post&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
